---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Mosskeep Frog" description="A colourful moss-backed frog of Vaelinya.">
  <section class="page-section animal-sheet-page">
    <article class="panel animal-sheet">
      <div class="animal-sheet-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">World · Animals</p>
        <h1>Mosskeep Frog</h1>
        <p class="lede">A colourful blue-green-gold frog with a living moss garden growing across its back.</p>

        <dl class="animal-facts">
          <div>
            <dt>What it is</dt>
            <dd>A small wetland creature of moss, shade, stone, and quiet water.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Where it lives</dt>
            <dd>Wet bridge stones, shaded pools, old walls, moss beds, tree roots, cave mouths, and damp path edges.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>How to recognise it</dt>
            <dd>Golden eyes, damp stone-coloured feet, blue-green-gold skin, violet flowers, seed capsules, dew-orbs, and fern fronds in the moss on its back.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Sound and movement</dt>
            <dd>A low wet chirrup, like one drop of water landing in moss. It moves in short careful hops from stone to root to moss patch.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>What it does</dt>
            <dd>It carries moisture, moss spores, fern-specks, wetland seed-life, and small insects between damp places.</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>

        <p class="access-note"><strong>Accessibility note:</strong> Mosskeep Frogs are colourful blue-green-gold frogs with golden eyes and living moss gardens on their backs.</p>

        <nav class="animal-links" aria-label="Related animal pages">
          <a href="/world/animals/amethyst-orblight/">Amethyst Orblight</a>
          <a href="/world/animals/hearthcrest-caller/">Hearthcrest Caller</a>
          <a href="/world/animals/">Animals of Vaelinya</a>
        </nav>
      </div>

      <figure class="animal-sheet-art">
        <picture>
          <source
            media="(max-width: 560px)"
            srcset="/assets/images/vaelinya/animals/mosskeep-frog-v01-512-q.png"
          />
          <source
            media="(max-width: 900px)"
            srcset="/assets/images/vaelinya/animals/mosskeep-frog-v01-768-q.png"
          />
          <img
            src="/assets/images/vaelinya/animals/mosskeep-frog-v01-1024-q.png"
            alt="Mosskeep Frog, a colourful blue-green-gold frog with golden eyes and a living moss garden of tiny flowers, seed pods, and dew-orbs growing across its back."
            loading="eager"
            decoding="async"
            width="1024"
            height="1024"
          />
        </picture>
        <figcaption>Transparent cutout asset. Page text explains the important colour, sound, movement, and role.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </article>
  </section>

  <style>
    .animal-sheet-page {
      max-width: 980px;
      margin-inline: auto;
    }

    .animal-sheet {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.05fr) minmax(260px, 0.8fr);
      gap: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
      align-items: start;
      padding: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    }

    .animal-sheet .lede {
      max-width: 52ch;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .animal-facts {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.75rem;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }

    .animal-facts div {
      padding-block: 0.65rem;
      border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink, #211a33) 12%, transparent);
    }

    .animal-facts dt {
      margin-bottom: 0.18rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: var(--ink, #211a33);
    }

    .animal-facts dd {
      margin: 0;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .access-note {
      margin: 1rem 0 0;
      padding: 0.75rem 0;
      border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink, #211a33) 12%, transparent);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .animal-links {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.55rem;
      margin-top: 0.85rem;
    }

    .animal-links a {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      min-height: 40px;
      padding: 0.55rem 0.85rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: color-mix(in srgb, #fff4be 82%, white);
      border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink, #211a33) 14%, transparent);
      font-weight: 750;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .animal-sheet-art {
      margin: 0;
      padding: clamp(0.5rem, 1.6vw, 0.85rem);
      border-radius: 1.4rem;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at 72% 18%, rgba(255, 228, 132, 0.55), transparent 34%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 18% 80%, rgba(65, 210, 190, 0.25), transparent 36%),
        linear-gradient(145deg, rgba(255, 246, 218, 0.44), rgba(157, 232, 207, 0.2));
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    }

    .animal-sheet-art img {
      display: block;
      width: min(100%, 360px);
      height: auto;
      margin-inline: auto;
      filter: drop-shadow(0 18px 28px rgba(22, 14, 39, 0.2));
    }

    .animal-sheet-art figcaption {
      max-width: 36ch;
      margin: 0.55rem auto 0;
      color: var(--muted, #574d68);
      font-size: 0.86rem;
      line-height: 1.45;
      text-align: center;
    }

    @media (max-width: 820px) {
      .animal-sheet {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .animal-sheet-art {
        order: -1;
      }

      .animal-sheet-art img {
        width: min(100%, 320px);
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
